twooter

Class TwooterEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • twooter.TwooterEvent

  • public class TwooterEvent
extends java.lang.Object
    When subscribed to Twooter live feed events, a series of this object type will be created and passed to the listening code. It is recommended that you implement and set-up the interface before starting the live feed, otherwise some events will be lost.

      • type

        public final int type
        Defines the type of event this is, should be one of the following constants: { CONNECT, DISCONNECT, MESSAGE, USER, or TAG } Immutable (cannot be changed)

      • payload

        public final java.lang.String payload
        Defines the payload for this event. Immutable (cannot be changed) For MESSAGE events, this is the message unique identifier, for USER events, this is the username, and for TAG events, this is the tag string.

      • time

        public final long time
        The timestamp from when this event occurred (client-side timestamp) as a UNIX timestamp in seconds. UNIX times are expressed as the total number of seconds since 00:00:00 1 January 1970. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unix_time for more details. Immutable (cannot be changed)
